ccre.cluck_old

Class CluckEncoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • ccre.cluck_old.CluckEncoder

  • public class CluckEncoder
extends java.lang.Object
    A CluckEncoder provides a number of methods for publishing and subscribing to various dynamic objects, such as channels, events, loggers, and holders.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  CluckEncoder.AvailableListener
      An AvailableListener is notified whenever a new object is provided on the network that it did not previously know about.

    • Method Detail

      • searchAndSubscribePublished

        public void searchAndSubscribePublished(CluckEncoder.AvailableListener listener)
        Register a AvailableListener to listen for new objects on the network, and ask all other encoders to resend their lists of what objects they provide.
        Parameters:
        listener - The AvailableListener to subscribe to responses.

      • searchPublished

        public void searchPublished()
        Tell all encoders on the network to resend their lists of objects. These will be picked up by any AvailableListeners on the network. Use in combination with clearRecord() to relist everything.
        See Also:
        CluckEncoder.AvailableListener.clearRecord()

      • unsubscribePublished

        public void unsubscribePublished(CluckEncoder.AvailableListener listener)
        Unsubscribe an AvailableListener from listening to objects on the network. It will no longer be notified of the existence of any objects.
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to remove.

      • publishTunableFloat

        public void publishTunableFloat(java.lang.String name,
                       FloatTuner tune,
                       java.lang.String targetref)
        Publish a FloatTuner that allows for it to be easily tuned remotely. Also takes an optional argument that represents a previously shared channel that should be the default tuning target (a published FloatInputProducer).
        Parameters:
        name - the name to put the tuning under.
        tune - the FloatTuner to share.
        targetref - (optional) the name of the FloatInputProducer to use as a default.

      • subscribeTunableFloat

        public FloatTuner subscribeTunableFloat(java.lang.String name)
        Subscribe to a FloatStatus and return a FloatTuner for easy tuning.
        Parameters:
        name - the name to look for the tuning under.
        Returns:
        the FloatTuner that has been received.

      • subscribeBooleanInputProducer

        public BooleanInput subscribeBooleanInputProducer(java.lang.String name,
                                         boolean default_)
        Subscribe to a BooleanInputProducer from the network. This can be listened to, which will be notified when the original published BooleanInputProducer change. This method returns a BooleanInput instead of a BooleanInputProducer - it keeps track of the current value, defaulting to the default_ parameter before any data is received.
        Parameters:
        name - the name to look for the object under.
        default_ - the boolean to set this to by default.
        Returns:
        the BooleanInputProducer that has been received.
        See Also:
        publishBooleanInputProducer(java.lang.String, ccre.chan.BooleanInputProducer)

      • publishStringHolder

        public void publishStringHolder(java.lang.String name,
                       StringHolder strh)
        Publish a StringHolder to the network. This will synchronize the StringHolder with all other registered StringHolders of the same name. This is the same as a call to registerWithoutPullStringHolder, except that it also overwrites the current value on the network with this StringHolder's value.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the StringHolder
        strh - the StringHolder to register

      • registerStringHolder

        public void registerStringHolder(java.lang.String name,
                        StringHolder strh)
        Register a StringHolder on the network. This will synchronize the StringHolder with all other registered StringHolders of the same name. This is the same as a call to registerWithoutPullStringHolder, except that it also requests the current value from another node on the network.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the StringHolder
        strh - the StringHolder to register

      • registerWithoutPullStringHolder

        public void registerWithoutPullStringHolder(java.lang.String name,
                                   StringHolder strh)
        Register a StringHolder on the network. This will synchronized the StringHolder with all other registered StringHolders of the same name. This will not send the current value or request a current value from anything on the network. Use publishStringHolder or registerStringHolder for that.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the StringHolder
        strh - the StringHolder to register

      • subscribeWithoutPullStringHolder

        public StringHolder subscribeWithoutPullStringHolder(java.lang.String name,
                                            java.lang.String default_)
        Subscribe to a StringHolder on the network. This will synchronize the StringHolder with all other registered StringHolders of the same name. This is the same as a call to registerWithoutPullStringHolder, except that it creates a StringHolder beforehand.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the StringHolder
        default_ - the default value of the new StringHolder (does not override anything on the network)
        Returns:
        the newly registered StringHolder.

      • subscribeStringHolder

        public StringHolder subscribeStringHolder(java.lang.String name,
                                 java.lang.String default_)
        Subscribe to a StringHolder on the network. This will synchronize the StringHolder with all other registered StringHolders of the same name. This is the same as a call to registerStringHolder, except that it creates a StringHolder beforehand.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the StringHolder
        default_ - the default value of the new StringHolder (does not override anything on the network)
        Returns:
        the newly registered StringHolder.
